name: SAGA Coffee Renon - Listening Space
address: Jl. Ciung Wanara I No.23, Sumerta Kelod, Kec. Denpasar Tim., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80234, Indonesia
review 1:
The thing I love about this cafe is the food!!! They have very very delicious food. My favorite is the Siomay, idk how but its soo gooood. The beverage is fine, they have non dairy milk option too. The smoothies are tasty. They are quited pricey tho.

This cafe is good if you are looking for a place to sit, working, and eating. The only problem is the AC doesnt really work when we were there, and also its a bit noisy so not recommend for online meeting.

Overall, nice cafe for hang out and do your work a bit.
review 2:
It's a great place to hang out with your friends or to get some offline work done.
It's way too noisy to have work/video calls.
The coffee is good, and the food is average. The pastry is fresh and tastes best out of the food options. The space is well arranged and feels very home-like.
review 3:
A comfy homey coffee shop that as someone with a toddler really loves. I can let my 2yo roam around and be happy and safe here.

The place have a really homey vibe and have games you can play while you are here. I saw also a couple people that was working here.

Their coffee are good and the food options are also plentiful and also tasty. They have reasonable prices too

This can be a favourite place to come for me and my family
review 4: It was nice, the place is cozy and warm. Such a good place to hangout with your friends. I gave three stars cos one of the staff (a girl) was kinda  harsh. It was not completely rude but kinda more like annoying. The way she‚Äôs staring at me and my friends when she delivered our order is just not a pleasant experience for us. But overall the foods are good and the cookies kinda taste like spices probably because they use the same microwave to heat other foods, IDK.
review 5:
The coffe is good üëç
But the food that i eat just standard taste.
Yakimesi rice with chicken karage, the chicken is to dry and the rice dont really have a taste.
But the cafe have a good atmosphere, good place for hang out with friends.

name: Nasi Ayam Kedewatan Ibu Mangku - Renon (Cabang I)
address: Jl. Tukad Badung No.11, Renon, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80234, Indonesia
review 1:
One of their best vibes branch. I prefer the quality of food in here rather than in Seminyak. The best Nasi Ayam in Bali, you can also request to separate spicy sauce if you can‚Äôt bear the spiciness level.

I love the vibes and their outdoor area. They also have small playground for kids too and fish pond
review 2:
Love the natural vibes at this spot ‚Äì fish ponds, cobblestones, vines, and plants create a garden-like escape where greenery surrounds you. The ambiance is refreshing.

Now, let's talk food ‚Äì they nail it! Tried the Nasi Ayam Kedewatan, and it's a delightful mix of rice, veggies, and chicken. Authentic Balinese flavors that hit the spot. A tasty trip to Bali right here. üåøüçõ
review 3:
From all the restaurants we've been to, this is the champion.
Everything is perfect. The taste, atmosphere,and staff are amazing.
I highly recommend this restaurant if you want to try real Balinese food.
review 4:
Tasty nasi campur and ayam betutu, also one vegetarian option available.
Outside dining in a beautiful and peaceful garden.
review 5:
what i really like about this place is that they incorporate natural elements into their restaurant. they have fish ponds, cobblestones, vines, and plants. it feels like you step into a garden where it's green everywhere.

the food here is delicious. it's fun because you can eat different kinds of chicken dishes in small portions, so you can taste many flavors. i'm not a fan of their chicken gizzard, though. it's too chewy. but other than that, it's perfect to eat with rice and betutu sauce.

if you're a moslem, they also have a praying room albeit not too large. but that wouldn't be a problem since many places in bali don't have a praying room for moslem.

name: Bestah Coliving
address: Jl. Tukad Yeh Sungi I, Renon, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80234, Indonesia
review 1: Good location in the city center, but inside rather small alley, like an oasis. Nice pool. Good system with central lock in front door. Quick check in.
review 2: Great hotel! Each room has a personal router, which is helpful considering almost all things are done online. The staff was also very friendly! Room is clean, and has a smart tv :D Anyways, i enjoyed my stay here. Thanks for the experience!
review 3: Very good place for that prices. Clean and comfortable rooms, very good common space with good kitchen. It was very fun place to stay. Can meet good people there for sure.
review 4: his centrally located apartment is a gem in the heart of the city. Its prime location offers easy access to all the major attractions, restaurants, and entertainment options. The apartment itself is stylishly designed and thoughtfully furnished, providing a comfortable and inviting living space. The open floor plan creates a sense of spaciousness, while large windows fill the rooms with natural light and offer stunning city views. The amenities provided are top-notch, including a well-equipped gym, a relaxing rooftop pool, and a cozy lounge area. The security measures are excellent, ensuring a safe and secure environment for residents. The management team is attentive and responsive, always ready to assist with any concerns or requests. Whether you're a busy professional or a small family, this apartment offers convenience and convenience and a vibrant city lifestyle. Experience the urban living at its finest by choosing this centrally located apartment as your home away from home.
review 5:
Stayed here for a few weeks,
Amazing team and staff and rooms are super clean 100% recommend

name: Samana Residence Denpasar
address: Jalan Ciung Wanara II No. 29, Sumerta Kelod, Renon, Denpasar Selatan, Denpasar City, Bali 80226, Indonesia
review 1: One of the worst hotel experience. We orderes "superior double room", when we first entered a room, we saw many spider webs all around ceiling, bed sheets were full of yellow stains, so we asked to change room. Reception agreed with that and showed us another one. In this one bathroom has not been cleaned after last guests, we found used toiletries in the shower, bed sheets were also full of stains and overall room was not cleaned properly. So we asked in reception to change sheets and clean bathroom. They agreed with that but there was no apology for that and they didn't rush to clean the room. After sheets were changed we saw that pillow sheet has holes from smoking and there still was stains on sheets but we didn't bother any more. Also our towels had stains. After night we saw that bathroom ceiling was leaking with some brownish liquid righ by the toilet. Overall disgusting hotel, sad that nobody really cares about customers.
review 2:
Honestly don‚Äôt know where all the good reviews are coming from.
Worst place I ever stayed. Dirty sheets, we had to ask to replace them.
Bugs and little flies everywhere. Sink and shower head full with lime stones and didn‚Äôt seem really clean. Thank god we only stayed one night. Don‚Äôt be fooled by the pictures!
review 3:
One of the receptionists is very rude and has no attitude at all. Shouting at me as the guest when I was trying to tell her in a polite way because every time I asked her, she always said "I don't know" without even staring at my face.

And yesterday I tried to tell her, but she cut me off while talking and told me sorry for cutting you off because you sat there on the chair in front of the receptionist while there's another guest checked in and based on the SOP you were wrong and not supposed to sit there, I could have warned you earlier (with a high tone) and I for sure replied her as she didn't respect me as a guest "oh wow your tone was really rude and you weren't supposed to treat other guest like this etc, you're not supposed to speak in a high intonation to me as I'm the guest here".

I've been staying here for 4 months now, but this lady named pipin doesn't seem to respect each guest who has been staying there longer.

The lady named pipin is very rude and she's not supposed to work in the hospitality industry.

I have no complaints about other staff, they are all friendly and polite except for that one lady that I mentioned above.
review 4: The room is clean but the ambience is more like a boarding house which is still acceptable.
review 5: I usually write a long review but I will keep it short and sweet. The place is squeaky clean, staff friendly, comfortable bed, owner who wants to know how she can make the place better. All the ingredients necessary for an enduring good experience. Often I read a review and it doesn‚Äôt match my experience. I think it may be my standards but also many reviews are old and the place goes down hill.  Not here.  I will bet that this place will only get better.  I should also say the location is outstanding, quiet, clean and upscale neighborhood. Two thumbs way up.

name: Warung Be Pasih
address: Jl. Pemuda III No.24, Renon, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80239, Indonesia
review 1: Good was delicious and worth the money. Place is spacious and clean. Servers were sweet. Worth to try if you enjoy eating fish. üòÅ
review 2:
Just love our choice, Fish satay and Be Pasih Bakar sambal Nyat-nyat. Food come with smooth and light fish soup and side dish plecing kangkung. All the food was fresh

In several minute si Mbok was serving the food come with her hospitality.
And the all the menu are affordable

Will come back for sure

review 4: Shout out to my friend who takes me here and shouts out for this restaurant cuz even the rice taste soooo good and legit. I love love love that
review 5: The fish steak at this restaurant is unparalleled, especially when paired with the delightful sambal matah ‚Äì a perfect combination. It has consistently remained my favorite dining spot in Bali.

name: Okinawa Sushi Bali
address: Jl. Moh. Yamin V Link. Sembung Sari No.Br, Sumerta Kelod, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80239, Indonesia
review 1:
Place as a building is beautiful. Very clean and nice. The menu is gigantic and very complicated. There is a lack of sets which would make it easier for sharing. There is also no English menu, so use Google translate only. Staff does not speak English also.
As for food we ordered a mix of things. The tuna on nigiri wassliced so thin it was almost transparent, the salmon similar. Tamago however beautiful and thick. Gyu truffle meat was delicious! the sushi rolls.. well choice is very Indonesian focused on meats.. the California roll was drowning in mayonnaise- drowning!. Spicy tuna roll was covered in bread crumbs which dominated the taste and really took away from the rolls. Shame that the service and medium food takes away from this place. I think there is no passion and absolutely no manager to take care of the place. Also best if you cover up the staffareaon the stairs as it looks like a trash can - such a mess..
Overall i would recommend coming here keeping in mind that only bahasa service and some tastes are different from what you know from Japan or Europe.
review 2:
I have to say, I enjoyed every single bite of the meal in (Okinawa Renon). I tried their new Fresh Oyster dish. Some was small some was a bit bigger and the taste is good and has great Presentation.

Considering the quality, the price is reasonable. Ideal for those who want a romantic night out. There was also plenty of room for bigger groups but make sure to book in advanced.

The manager lets us sit upstairs in the big table for big group even if there were just the 3 of us because I been here many times with my parents and ex-boyfriend from Slovakia and many other family members since they first opened so considering that, at least I felt comfortable and treated fairly because I am a long time coming back customer who lives here in Bali a very2 long time in Renon.

I recommend the Aburi Salmon Mentai üç£ yummy ü§§

So because of this nice, I will give 5 ‚ú®
üçÄLucky me!

PS: we really miss the first menu when you can pick many different mixed types of sushi and sashimi for fair price but now price had gone up for that but I used to come more often when they had that very first menu when you can pick a few sushi/sashimi and you get about 7 or 12 pieces for a super reasonable price. Hope they can do specials like that again some day then possibly I‚Äôll come more often üòã

üå∏ it was my American Husband‚Äôs first time here and he really likes the place even if he doesn‚Äôt like seafood because he is allergic but he said the place was great he ordered popcorn chicken rice or something like that and said he doesn‚Äôt mind coming back againüòÜ - my friend Asti likes to come here often too she said. üëçüèæüëçüèæüëçüèæ 5 STARS üåü SEE U SOON!!

We like the empire sushi & salmon kanape, their chuka idako is fresh n awesome. If you want to taste something else try their gyukatsu or their creamy ramen, creamy not so milky, n the broth is soothing your soul.

review 5:
One of the best sushi restaurant in Bali z

name: Roobs Bistro
address: Jl. Tukad Yeh Aya No.93, Dauh Puri Klod, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80234, Indonesia
review 1: Cool place to having a night‚Äôs out with friends ü´°

address: Jl. Pemuda II No.22, Sumerta Kelod, Kec. Denpasar Tim., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80239, Indonesia

name: Adikara
address: Jl. Ciungwanara II No.6, Sumerta Kelod, Kec. Denpasar Tim., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80234, Indonesia
review 1: Best room and affordable price

name: Resident Coffee and Tea
address: Jl. Pemuda VI No.4, Renon, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80239, Indonesia
review 1:
We tried the V60 Japanese of Pulu-Pulu and Solok.
Loved the taste of each! I can even taste the bark of tree in each sip.
Light meals only, not too bad.
I wish to spend longer time. The ambience is very calming and relaxing. Just like others said, a true hidden gem in Renon area.
review 2: Quite nice - ArchiHomy, good Coffee, comfy sitting & do working. Chic-Small house garden what Balinese touch, recommended !
review 3: A truly hidden gem in Renon area. Perfect place to read books with beautiful greenery surrounding and decent cup of coffee (I love Ice Cappuccino!)
review 4: What a cozy cafe around Renon! Homey design, good vibes, very comfortable to stay all day here to work or just have a chat with friends. They have tea, coffee, and chocolate drink options to enjoy, but for bites they only have dessert and non of them are vegan friendly. I tried the chocolate drink with oat milk, taste just ok, nothing special. Next time will try their tea series.
review 5: A homey coffee shop in the middle of Renon. It's located at an alley so people are not going to spot it from the main road. I like the ambiance, suitable for chilling, reading a book, or just daydreaming. It's not super suitable for working though, cause the dark and warm ambiance makes you sleepy. But there is a long wooden table where you can work on your laptop comfortably.

name: Shagida Apartment
address: Jl. Ciung Wanara I No.7, Sumerta Kelod, Kec. Denpasar Tim., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80234, Indonesia
review 1: This apartment exceeded my expectations! It was incredibly cozy and felt like a home away from home. Despite being affordable, it had all the amenities I needed, including a fully equipped kitchen. I would highly recommend it!
review 2: Budget homestay while you visit bali, located in Denpasar, and it will be easy for you to get some food around, mostly indonesian food, but the most interesting one is fish grill menu that not to far from it.
review 3: Really great apartment, or u can call it high class koskosan with fairly affordable price, the only problem is wifi connection, urgently needed a change!
review 4: Budget apartment in Bali, for daily, weekly or monthly. Nice and kind staffs, spacious parking, strategic location (city centre), with affordable prices...
review 5: Nice rooms. Clean enough. But, wifi a bit slows.

name: BUBURKU
address: Gg. V No.8, Panjer, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80234, Indonesia
review 1:
Very delicious
Traditional food that is rarely found
It runs out quickly, I've been here 3x before I got it
You can order online or come directly to the location

The marrow pulp and salak seeds are soft
The black sticky rice is sweet
The brown sugar is not too sweet
Plus delicious coconut milk
Mix in one spoonful
review 2: Affordable price and yummy, highly recommended!

name: Taman Janggan Renon Denpasar
address: Jl. Raya Puputan No.10, Sumerta Kelod, Kec. Denpasar Tim., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80239, Indonesia
review 1:
Although it looks like it's out of date, it is still a decent outdoor playground for the kids.

If you have 2.5 years old kids below, please give some supervision. You need to watch them properly, because not all of the features are for them. Some of them are for 3 years old up.

It is located at the heart of Denpasar, Renon. Where you are actually near almost everything.
review 2: An amazing playground for our children in the middle of the city. The place is truly cozy for both parents and kids as the design of its 'roof' is perfect; protecting its visitors from the extreme heat of Bali so it is still enjoyable even in the daylight. Truly recommended.
review 3: I don‚Äôt stay in the center point, because I avoid crowded places and choose the quiet spot. And this is a good infrastructure for children and family
review 4: This playground was built near the sports area in Renon. Nice & Safe place to bring toddlers (age 2-6 yo) to play. Thanks to the government for the "A" quality of the playground's materials. Good job!
review 5: It's a good place to play for kids with a soft pad as the floor. And it's free to go here. Thanks for the government who care much for our kids so we can bring them play here everyday. The minus point is just about the location which is near the big street, so we cannot avoid our kids from bad air around. There are some spots here which we can use to relax and also there are some exercise equipment for us to break our stress from working. But again it needs some attention so it won't be broken easily.

name: Go Pang Bali
address: Jl. Tukad Yeh Aya No.95, Dauh Puri Klod, Kec. Denpasar Bar., Kota Denpasar, Bali 80234, Indonesia
review 1:
My second visit, and I still recommend this place as the best AYCE restaurant in town
Tom yam soup is my favorite üòç
Thanks for the friendly staff who always there to fulfill our request üëçüèª
review 2:
Undrated korean bbq but WOOOOWWWW
Although have been passing this place manytime, it is just because it was not really tempting fron outside.
Once you got here, you will obviously come back!
The staff are amazing too, the service is great and they could recommend anything if you didn‚Äôt know what to takes üëå
Atmosphere is great as well ‚ú® open area but organized and looks amazing
Food? They served good quality of meats üëåhubby and I enjoyed very much.. ah the kimchi is the best, their tomyam stock is nice ‚ù§Ô∏è
review 3:
A fun place to eat where you cook your own food and soup on a couple of gas powered cookers.  Food was frozen though and the prawns not worth the extra expense!

All you can eat and includes ice cream & Es Teh
review 4: Affordable Korean BBQ all you can eat place. There is only one choice of beef for the regular package. The premium package includes beef belly. The staff number is minimal so they are not attentive and tend to forget our orders. Nice open air place suitable for BBQ.
review 5: The food was very good for what you pay. I thought you have to finish within 1.5 hour but turns out you can get anything more within those time and that's more than enough time to be honest. The beef was a bit frozen but it was good. The suki was also fresh and perfect. Price is great and in prime location right outside Lapangan Bajra Sandhi. The staffs was also friendly.  Will definitely come back.

name: Cityzen Renon Hotel
address: Jl. Ciungwanara II No.2, Panjer, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80234, Indonesia
review 1: The room I stayed was designed for someone taller (170cm+), the towels were washed when it has many dirty "stuff" on it. The toilet has mold all over. The pros: staffs are very nice, hot water is the best and aplenty, room is very big and adequately lit.
review 2:
There are pros and cons to this hotel. My overall stay was very pleasant however. I stayed in a single room. Affordable. Not expensive.
The staff were incredibly helpful and very nice. They even lent me an adapter for my laptop for free.
The AC is great. The bed is quite comfortable also. Toothbrush and toothpaste are available. Shampoo and conditioner included.
The location is very convenient. There are many many small grocery shops and food shops all over the area within walking distance. The Royal Thai Embassy is a 5 minute walk from the hotel.

As nice as the staff and location was there were also cons. No refrigerator. No drinking water(you have to go out to buy your own water or buy from the hotel). There is no sink in the bathroom which was very odd. The outlet next to the bed is under the small table on the left which I had to lay down flat to reach(not the end of the world but very inconvenient).
review 3:
Cigarette mold smell, mold on pillows, ants in bed. Bloodstains and hair on bedsheets.
I have quite high tolerance but wow, this was next level. Hotel across street has same price and clean rooms.
review 4: Good place to stay in the mid of Denpasar town. Friendly staff, clean hotel, good for backpacker.
review 5: Very cheap in the heart of Denpasar. Wi-Fi kept cutting out for no reason, but other than that the room we stayed in was huge and there was a kettle and tea making facilities

name: Bubur Ayam Pak Lik
address: Jl. Raya Puputan, Panjer, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80234, Indonesia
review 1:
On List! Best Chicken Porridge / Bubur Ayam in Bali

The chicken porridge so tasty and very flavorful. The only thing that shocking me was that the spoon for eating was immediately put into the bowl of porridge, not on the table.

Mr. Lik helped those at the cashier not hesitate to help staff who were handling busy orders. What a great leader.

Very strategic location, right in front of the Lapangan Brajasandhi Puputan Renon

I ordered two mung-bean porridge to take home, and it wasn't bad. Next, I want to try the vegetable rice cake and fried chicken.
review 2: Not so authentic chicken porridge. Small portion, no vegetables, only slice eggs, shredded chicken, yellow broth, bawang goreng on the top. But I love their Lontong sayur, but a little bit oily. Mostly people come in the morning for breakfast. They also have ayam goreng, rawon, etc.
review 3: Other than bubur ayam, they also provide various menu for breakfast. Actually the location is strategic for breakfast craving after finished the morning jogging. However, you need to go a bit go narrow to find this place.
review 4: Opposite Banjra Sandhi. On sunday, they hv car free event. All people been walking and also have stalls/hawkers selling food n goods
review 5: i think that this is the best Jakarta's style Porridge so far, the owner's and the staffs are friendly too.

name: Puri Tresna Villas
address: Jl. Pemuda III No.30, Renon, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80239, Indonesia
review 1: Best place for taking preweed pic I ever seen. Many good spot and place for that. The photographer also very patient with the client even take a longtime. Very recommend it place...the staff very friendly
review 2: What a lovely exotic place...... one day I believe it will become a heritage of this beautiful island. Nice owner indeed...... review 3:
One of the prettiest place in Bali. This puri/palace is actually an open-space studio with actual balinese style building for photoshoot on any occassion. Most of the time this place was used to shoot prewedding photoshoot.
The price for 1.5 hour is 700k rupiah.
review 4: Overall it is a beautiful 'puri'/palace. Lots of pre-wedding photo sessions taken in this location.
review 5: Best place for photoshoots, especially for pre wedding, staffs were friendly & polite, you can book the place on the spot.

name: Visaya Residence
address: Jl. Tukad Ayung No.36, Renon, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80234, Indonesia
review 1: Perfect for business vacation. Calm but located in the core of city. The Pool make you reduce your tiring. And services people at there so kindness. So you can feel comfort as like a family. Thank You Visaya.
review 3: Nice rate, nice room, nice view, good service

name: kedai 99
address: Jl. Ciung Wanara VI No.10, Renon, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80234, Indonesia
review 1: Chinese food style Surabaya, the taste is really good, the place is cool and clean, the service is fast, every time we go to Denpasar we definitely stop here.  wide parking
review 2: Kedai 99 is a Chinese food cuisine and really delicious. I tried all 3 dishes and the taste was delicious. I really recommend this place. FYI, there is no aircon ya. Sometimes we must try eating food in a normal area like outdoor style, so you can get the experience between indoor and outdoor style.
review 3:

review 5: Place : average food : delicious price : a little bit high for an average place . atmosphere : average( too hot , outdoor , with only small fan . ) quite not too noisy . They also do delivery service ( don‚Äôt worry for delivery fee if you live near , they will deliver it for free ! )

name: Iwagumi Sushi Renon
address: GAIA Studio, Jl. Tukad Badung No.6C Lt. I Gedung, Renon, Denpasar Selatan, Kota Denpasar, Bali 80226, Indonesia
review 1: Once I tried to dine in there at 12 pm and the staff said they started at 1 pm. It was quite late to get lunch around that time so I skipped it. Then I tried to order for birthday at home and the service was satisfying. The orders arrive safely and the taste was nice. The mochi is very delicious and the taste is just right.
review 2: Affordable price, aesthetic place, fast service and delicious foods
review 3: good food, great service, nice place, affordable price. new favorite place!
review 5: Such a cute place with delicious affordable sushi and ramen!
